  "documentType": "registered_will",
  "commonIssues": "<div class=\"accordion\" id=\"issueAccordion\"> <div class=\"card mb-2\"><div class=\"card-header\" id=\"heading1\"><h5 class=\"mb-0\"><button class=\"btn btn-link text-left\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#collapse1\" style=\"white-space: normal; word-break: break-word;\"><i class=\"fas fa-chevron-right mr-2\"></i>Witness and Beneficiary Conflicts</button></h5></div> <div id=\"collapse1\" class=\"collapse\"><div class=\"card-body\"><p>Using a beneficiary as a witness makes their bequest legally void.</p><p><strong>How to fix:</strong></p><ul><li>Ensure the two attesting witnesses are completely independent and receive nothing under the Will.</li></ul></div></div></div> <div class=\"card mb-2\"><div class=\"card-header\" id=\"heading2\"><h5 class=\"mb-0\"><button class=\"btn btn-link text-left collapsed\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#collapse2\" style=\"white-space: normal; word-break: break-word;\"><i class=\"fas fa-chevron-right mr-2\"></i>Technical Issues with e-Requisition</button></h5></div> <div id=\"collapse2\" class=\"collapse\"><div class=\"card-body\"><p>Generating and managing the 30-day valid e-Assessment slip.</p><p><strong>How to fix:</strong></p><ul><li>Carefully use the <a href=\"https://wbregistration.gov.in/\" target=\"_blank\">WB Registration Portal</a>. Pay fees via GRIPS before the slip expires.</li></ul></div></div></div> <div class=\"card mb-2\"><div class=\"card-header\" id=\"heading3\"><h5 class=\"mb-0\"><button class=\"btn btn-link text-left collapsed\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#collapse3\" style=\"white-space: normal; word-break: break-word;\"><i class=\"fas fa-chevron-right mr-2\"></i>Mandatory Probate in Kolkata</button></h5></div> <div id=\"collapse3\" class=\"collapse\"><div class=\"card-body\"><p>Even registered Wills face severe post-death delays because Probate is mandatory in Kolkata.</p><p><strong>How to fix:</strong></p><ul><li>Beneficiaries must apply to the High Court or District Court for Probate, presenting the original Will and witness testimonies.</li></ul></div></div></div> <div class=\"card mb-2\"><div class=\"card-header\" id=\"heading4\"><h5 class=\"mb-0\"><button class=\"btn btn-link text-left collapsed\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#collapse4\" style=\"white-space: normal; word-break: break-word;\"><i class=\"fas fa-chevron-right mr-2\"></i>Suspicious Circumstances & Forgery</button></h5></div> <div id=\"collapse4\" class=\"collapse\"><div class=\"card-body\"><p>Challenges arising from the exclusion of natural heirs or beneficiary's active role.</p><p><strong>How to fix:</strong></p><ul><li>Beneficiaries should not participate in the drafting or registration process. Ensure a medical certificate is attached.</li></ul></div></div></div> <div class=\"card mb-2\"><div class=\"card-header\" id=\"heading5\"><h5 class=\"mb-0\"><button class=\"btn btn-link text-left collapsed\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#collapse5\" style=\"white-space: normal; word-break: break-word;\"><i class=\"fas fa-chevron-right mr-2\"></i>Registration Refusal Appeals</button></h5></div> <div id=\"collapse5\" class=\"collapse\"><div class=\"card-body\"><p>The Sub-Registrar may refuse registration if unsatisfied with the testator's capacity.</p><p><strong>How to fix:</strong></p><ul><li>File an appeal to the Registrar within 30 days of the refusal order.</li></ul></div></div></div></div>"
}
